Reading sporting director, Mark Bowen has agreed on a deal with the club to become their new head coach as reported by Sky Sports on Monday. Bowen will replace Jose Gomes, who was sacked last week, at the Madejski Stadium. The 55-year-old will be assisted by former Chelsea goalkeeper, Eddie Niedzwiecki at the Royals. He joined Reading in March as a technical director and was promoted to his current role of sporting director in the summer. DAILY POST recalls that Gomes was sacked following their 1-0 defeat to Bristol City in the Championship some few days ago.  Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.